TITLE: Existing home sales unexpectedly fall in March, reversing recent gains
SUMMARY: Sales of previously owned homes fell 2.2% in March from the prior month due to higher mortgage rates, according to the National Association of Realtors

TITLE: Bilt Rewards offers first-ever loyalty program to earn points on rent
SUMMARY: Bilt Rewards founder and CEO Ankur Jain joins 'The Claman Countdown' to discuss their rewards program that turns points into a down payment on a home.&nbsp

TITLE: CSX train derails near Chicago, crushing several vehicles: reports
SUMMARY: A transport train operated by CSX became derailed on Wednesday night in Blue Island, Illinois, just south of Chicago

SUMMARY: ESPRIT Holdings CEO William Pak discusses the launch of the fashion company's rebrand on 'The Claman Countdown

TITLE: Michelin recalls more than 500K tires that do not meet snow traction requirements
SUMMARY: Michelin is recalling around 542,000 tires after testing revealed they fail to meet federal regulations for snow tires in the U.S. and Canada

TITLE: Disney plans layoffs for thousands next week, report says
SUMMARY: Walt Disney Co. reportedly will cut thousands of jobs across the company by next week, including those at theme parks, in entertainment and on corporate teams

TITLE: Americans spent more on legal cannabis in 2022 than chocolate, beer: report
SUMMARY: Americans are spending more money on legal cannabis purchases than they are spending on chocolate, craft beer, opioid medications or topical pain relief

SUMMARY: David's Bridal CEO Jim Marcum discusses how the nation's largest wedding outfit retailer can survive bankruptcy on 'The Claman Countdown

TITLE: King Charles III's coronation boosts UK tourism as region still recovering from lockdowns
SUMMARY: British officials said they believe King Charles III's coronation will help boost the tourism industry that is still reeling from two years of COVID-19 restrictions

TITLE: Companies' cost inflation is slowing but shoppers may wait for lower prices
SUMMARY: Cost inflation rose during the COVID-19 pandemic and was exacerbated by Russia's invasion of Ukraine, which sent energy prices to record highs last year
